practitioner.about:
Dr. Wahid Ahmad Fayad Koudsi is a General Practitioner at Medcare Medical Centre. He completed his MBBS from RAK Medical and Health Sciences University in Ras Al Khaimah, UAE.

After completing his graduation, Dr. Koudsi interned at the Emirates Health Services Facilities and then worked as a Teaching Assistant in the Internal Medicine Department at RAK Medical and Health Sciences University. Subsequently, he worked in collaboration with Sharjah Charity International as Medical Director of their medical centre and as a General Practitioner, he handled in-patient wards and Emergency department patients at Burjeel Specialty Hospital.

As a General Practitioner, Dr. Koudsi takes care of chronic and complex health conditions, ensures treatment of urgent and acute non-life-threatening diseases, preventive care including health education and immunisation, screening and early detection of disease, palliative care and referral to allied health professions for specialised medical care. He has successfully treated patients with pneumonia, pharyngitis, tonsillitis, infective gastroenteritis, scabies, eczema, tapeworms, H. pylori infection, GERD, diabetes, hypertension, UTI, benign prostatic hyperplasia, asthma, anaemia, otitis media, otitis externa, osteoarthritis, musculoskeletal injuries and conjunctivitis.

After spending hours at work, Dr. Koudsi likes to unwind by playing Football, Basketball, Tennis, and Padel. In his spare time, he enjoys reading too. He speaks Arabic and English.

locations.about:
Medcare Medical Centre in Tilal Al Ghaf is a premium, advanced healthcare facility devoted to meeting the diverse healthcare needs of its community. This inviting medical centre prioritizes comfort and convenience, offering cutting-edge facilities and comprehensive medical services. A key highlight is our state-of-the-art physiotherapy and rehabilitation centre, which provides advanced treatments for restoring and enhancing functional abilities and quality of life. This makes it ideal for patients of all ages seeking precise diagnoses and prompt treatment across various specialties.

At the core of Medcare Medical Centre Tilal Al Ghaf is a team of multicultural, multilingual doctors, complemented by exceptionally trained and experienced nurses and medical staff. The centre takes pride in its extensive array of advanced equipment, enabling its highly skilled medical team to provide top-tier care to all patients.

Experience the warmth of family-centric care delivered by our highly talented medical and non-medical staff. At Medcare Medical Centre Tilal Al Ghaf, we offer a range of services, including Family Medicine, Gynaecology, Paediatrics, Dermatology & Aesthetics, ENT, Rheumatology, and General Medicine. Additionally, we provide top-tier Orthopaedics, Physiotherapy, Radiology, and a gym as part of our rehabilitation centre.

Our dedicated Physio & Rehab Centre is a one-of-a-kind facility for physical medicine and rehabilitation, offering advanced treatment to restore and enhance functional abilities and quality of life. This includes care for those with mobility issues (especially post-surgery), physical, speech, and sensory impairments; injuries to the bones, ligaments, muscles, brain, and spine; and congenital neurological disorders. Led by a team of trained and qualified physical therapists and rehabilitation experts, this centre works in close collaboration with our orthopaedics department.

As part of our commitment to accessible healthcare, Medcare operates a network of four hospitals and over 25 multi-specialty medical centres across Dubai and Sharjah. Our goal is to provide reliable and timely medical care to our diverse clientele.
